1
00:00:10,172 --> 00:00:16,333


2
00:01:04,076 --> 00:01:07,687
I have found almost everything
ever written about love...

3
00:01:07,883 --> 00:01:09,127
...to be true.

4
00:01:09,323 --> 00:01:13,185
Shakespeare said,
"Journeys end in lovers meeting."

5
00:01:13,387 --> 00:01:15,110
What an extraordinary thought.

6
00:01:15,306 --> 00:01:18,601
Personally, I have not experienced
anything remotely close to that...

7
00:01:18,794 --> 00:01:21,729
...but I'm more than willing to believe
Shakespeare had.

8
00:01:21,930 --> 00:01:25,126
I suppose I think about love
more than anyone really should.

9
00:01:25,322 --> 00:01:30,537
I'm constantly amazed by its sheer
power to alter and define our lives.

10
00:01:30,794 --> 00:01:33,576
It was Shakespeare who also said,
"Love is blind."

11
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:38,664
Now, that is something
I know to be true.

12
00:01:50,024 --> 00:01:53,472
For some, quite inexplicably...

13
00:01:54,216 --> 00:01:55,710
...love fades.

14
00:02:09,959 --> 00:02:11,300
For others...

15
00:02:11,495 --> 00:02:13,502
...love is simply lost.

16
00:02:19,047 --> 00:02:23,040
But then, of course,
love can also be found.

17
00:02:24,230 --> 00:02:26,237
Even if just for the night.

18
00:02:31,045 --> 00:02:33,118
And then there'
another kind of love.

19
00:02:33,317 --> 00:02:34,692
The cruelest kind.

20
00:02:34,885 --> 00:02:37,503
The one that almost kills its victims.

21
00:02:37,701 --> 00:02:40,418
It' called unrequited love.

22
00:02:40,613 --> 00:02:44,541
Of that, I am an expert.

23
00:02:45,061 --> 00:02:48,704
Most love stories are about people
who fall in love with each other.

24
00:02:48,901 --> 00:02:52,096
But what about the rest of us?
What about our stories?

25
00:02:52,293 --> 00:02:54,593
Those of us who fall in love alone.

26
00:02:55,172 --> 00:02:57,725
We are the victims
of the one-sided affair.

27
00:02:57,923 --> 00:02:59,712
We are the cursed
of the loved ones.

28
00:02:59,908 --> 00:03:02,558
We are the unloved ones.
The walking wounded.

29
00:03:02,755 --> 00:03:06,072
The handicapped without the
advantage of a great parking space.

30
00:03:06,306 --> 00:03:08,641
Yes, you are looking at one
such individual.

31
00:03:08,834 --> 00:03:10,777
And I have willingly loved...

32
00:03:10,979 --> 00:03:14,623
...that man for over
three miserable years.

33
00:03:14,819 --> 00:03:17,022
The absolute worst years of my life.

34
00:03:17,218 --> 00:03:19,258
The worst Christmases,
the worst birthdays.

35
00:03:19,458 --> 00:03:22,970
New Year' Eves brought in
by tears and Valium.

36
00:03:23,171 --> 00:03:26,999
These years I've been in love have
been the darkest days of my life...

37
00:03:27,202 --> 00:03:30,267
...all because I'm cursed by being
in love with a man who does not...

38
00:03:30,465 --> 00:03:32,701
...and will not love me back.

39
00:03:32,897 --> 00:03:34,391
Oh, God, just the sight of him.

40
00:03:34,592 --> 00:03:37,941
Heart pounding, throat thickening,
absolutely can't swallow.

41
00:03:38,145 --> 00:03:40,698
All the usual symptoms.

42
00:03:40,897 --> 00:03:42,555
Oh, Jasper.

43
00:03:42,752 --> 00:03:47,029
- Don't tell me you're still...
- No, no, no, that's over. Very over.

44
00:03:47,232 --> 00:03:50,363
What's the story with you two anyway?
You were shagging him, werert you?

45
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:52,948
More importantly, I was in love
with him, truth be known.

46
00:03:53,152 --> 00:03:56,664
Then you found out he was shagging
that drip from Circulation.

47
00:03:56,864 --> 00:03:58,805
Which is when I stopped
shagging him.

48
00:03:59,007 --> 00:04:01,308
We shouldn't be talking
about this at the office party.

49
00:04:01,504 --> 00:04:03,772
But I always see you two together.

50
00:04:03,967 --> 00:04:06,618
He cheated on you,
but you stayed friends?

51
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:11,610
I was head over heels, you know?
Everyone knew.

52
00:04:11,807 --> 00:04:14,490
- Does it look like I'm crying right now?
- No, no, no.

53
00:04:14,687 --> 00:04:17,501
No, it just looks like it's the smoke
from my cigarette.

54
00:04:18,334 --> 00:04:21,084
Did he ever actually tell you
that he loved you back?

55
00:04:21,277 --> 00:04:25,368
Yes. Three, almost four times.
And when I reminded him of that...

56
00:04:25,566 --> 00:04:27,802
...he said it must have been an answer
to a question.

57
00:04:27,996 --> 00:04:31,193
Which, by the way,
it absolutely was not.

58
00:04:31,389 --> 00:04:35,349
You know, Iris, when you catch
your guy with another woman...

59
00:04:35,549 --> 00:04:37,556
...you're not supposed
to stay friends with him.

60
00:04:37,756 --> 00:04:39,764
You're supposed to never
talk to the prick again.

61
00:04:39,965 --> 00:04:43,096
You're supposed to throw things
at him, scream, call him names.

62
00:04:43,293 --> 00:04:44,787
Not do his blooming laundry.

63
00:04:44,988 --> 00:04:46,417
I don't do his laundry.

64
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:49,271
Did someone tell you
I do his laundry?

65
00:04:50,204 --> 00:04:51,578
No, no, all we do now is...

66
00:04:52,059 --> 00:04:54,165
...we e-mail.

67
00:04:54,364 --> 00:04:55,924
Not when he's with her, of course.

68
00:04:56,123 --> 00:04:59,571
Also when he's not with her,
we talk on the phone.

69
00:04:59,772 --> 00:05:03,994
Sometimes for hours. And then
there's the occasional long lunch.

70
00:05:04,187 --> 00:05:06,870
You know, I never realized
how pathetic you are.

71
00:05:07,066 --> 00:05:08,528
Really?

72
00:05:08,987 --> 00:05:11,801
Oh, God. I'm so aware of it.

73
00:05:11,994 --> 00:05:14,296
They always know just
how to get us, don't they?

74
00:05:14,681 --> 00:05:16,569
He knows whenever he wants
back in your life...

75
00:05:16,762 --> 00:05:19,663
Actually, he has made some small
comments like that recently.

76
00:05:19,866 --> 00:05:21,753
He hasn't exactly come
right out and said it...

77
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:23,768
Iris, did you file your story?

78
00:05:23,962 --> 00:05:28,217
Oh, no, not yet.
Down to the wire. Sorry.

79
00:05:28,793 --> 00:05:30,102
Better go.

80
00:05:32,569 --> 00:05:35,700
- Groom's best friend spoke...

81
00:05:35,897 --> 00:05:40,272
...for many guests
when he said, "Hilary...

82
00:05:41,593 --> 00:05:44,211
...will open Edward's eyes...

83
00:05:44,408 --> 00:05:47,637
...and round out his life."

84
00:05:47,831 --> 00:05:50,319
Okay, I've got a question for you.

85
00:05:54,072 --> 00:05:56,374
What's it like to be the only one
committed to work...

86
00:05:56,567 --> 00:05:58,061
...while the rest of us
are slumming?

87
00:05:58,264 --> 00:06:00,151
You mean what's it like
to be the only one...

88
00:06:00,343 --> 00:06:02,066
...not to finish their work on time?

89
00:06:02,264 --> 00:06:04,784
Hold on. Don't... Don't go.

90
00:06:05,335 --> 00:06:07,701
Is it fun having a brain
that works that fast?

91
00:06:07,894 --> 00:06:09,717
- Shut up.
- No, I mean it.

92
00:06:10,774 --> 00:06:12,683
Probably a brilliant finish too.

93
00:06:12,885 --> 00:06:14,861
I assure you it's not.

94
00:06:16,086 --> 00:06:19,021
- Hi, Simpkey.
- Hi.

95
00:06:21,525 --> 00:06:23,947
Your column today was fantastic.

96
00:06:24,149 --> 00:06:26,483
God, I loved that line:

97
00:06:26,933 --> 00:06:31,602
"The onrushing stripping of dignity
and thought from British lives."

98
00:06:32,278 --> 00:06:33,586
Great writing.

99
00:06:34,133 --> 00:06:36,237
Hey, I got you something
for Christmas.

100
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:39,851
That's convenient
because I got you something too.

101
00:06:42,356 --> 00:06:45,258
Darling, I don't actually
have my gift with me.

102
00:06:45,652 --> 00:06:48,499
In fact, I probably mislaid it,
but I know I got you something.

103
00:06:48,692 --> 00:06:51,212
I suspect it's somewhere in my car,
want to know what it is?

104
00:06:52,595 --> 00:06:54,766
No. No, no, that's okay.

105
00:06:54,964 --> 00:06:56,938
I know you're gonna look hot in it.

106
00:06:57,651 --> 00:06:59,790
Well, let's hope you find it, then.

107
00:07:00,564 --> 00:07:02,767
Not exactly something hot...

108
00:07:02,962 --> 00:07:05,646
...but happy Christmas.

109
00:07:07,443 --> 00:07:08,784
Thank you.

110
00:07:10,898 --> 00:07:13,200
I didn't think we'd get a chance
to do this this year.

111
00:07:13,394 --> 00:07:15,631
Remember last Christmas,
we exchanged gifts in March.

112
00:07:15,826 --> 00:07:17,484
This is good.

113
00:07:17,682 --> 00:07:19,372
We're getting better.

114
00:07:22,417 --> 00:07:23,944
You stinker.

115
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:28,559
It's a first edition.

116
00:07:28,753 --> 00:07:30,127
Where did you find it?

117
00:07:30,321 --> 00:07:34,347
Buried in that little place we found
in Covent Garden that time.

118
00:07:36,529 --> 00:07:38,764
Why are you so great?

119
00:07:40,689 --> 00:07:43,176
Everyone, can I have
your attention, please?

120
00:07:43,376 --> 00:07:45,710
Just a couple of minutes.
Thank you.

121
00:07:47,183 --> 00:07:49,485
I hate it that we can never talk.

122
00:07:51,151 --> 00:07:52,678
Hate it.

123
00:07:52,879 --> 00:07:56,491
Well, first of all, a very
happy Christmas to every one of you.

124
00:07:56,687 --> 00:07:57,767
Happy Christmas.

125
00:07:57,967 --> 00:08:01,513
Now, we're not officially closed,
as you very well know.

126
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:03,652
But we are going to try
and get by this week...

127
00:08:03,854 --> 00:08:06,408
...with a smaller-than-normal staff.

128
00:08:08,334 --> 00:08:10,221
Now, before some of you
rush off on holiday...

129
00:08:10,413 --> 00:08:14,026
...I do have one
rather important announcement.

130
00:08:14,222 --> 00:08:15,847
Now, this affects Iris.

131
00:08:16,046 --> 00:08:19,144
- Iris Simpkins, where are you?
- Here, sir.

132
00:08:19,341 --> 00:08:21,991
- Iris, I have a tip for you.
- Excellent.

133
00:08:22,189 --> 00:08:25,222
A wedding was privately
announced earlier today...

134
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:28,649
...that I don't believe any other paper
in town knows about.

135
00:08:28,844 --> 00:08:33,187
And I want you to be the first to report
on this particular union...

136
00:08:33,388 --> 00:08:38,177
...as it is between two of our
most esteemed colleagues.

137
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:42,122
May I introduce the newly engaged
Sarah Smith-Alcott...

138
00:08:42,316 --> 00:08:45,764
...and Jasper Bloom!

139
00:08:46,444 --> 00:08:48,418
Come on.

140
00:08:58,602 --> 00:09:01,602
If I had known this was going
to happen, I'd have worn my good suit.

141
00:10:55,939 --> 00:10:57,281
Amanda!

142
00:11:03,171 --> 00:11:04,796
Amanda.

143
00:11:07,714 --> 00:11:10,299
Look, may I just say again...

144
00:11:10,497 --> 00:11:12,734
...that I did not sleep with her?

145
00:11:12,929 --> 00:11:16,344
Right, because your receptionist
needs to work till 3 in the morning.

146
00:11:16,545 --> 00:11:19,544
A bunch of us were working all night.
She wanted to hang out.

147
00:11:19,746 --> 00:11:23,006
Okay. Then swear on my life
that you didn't sleep with her.

148
00:11:23,201 --> 00:11:24,761
Come on.

149
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,007
Go ahead.

150
00:11:26,208 --> 00:11:28,314
Look, I don't wanna...
I'm not gonna...

151
00:11:28,512 --> 00:11:30,138
Your receptionist, Ethan?

152
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:32,669
This is why I knew we were smart
never to get married.

153
00:11:32,864 --> 00:11:34,904
I told you never to get rid
of your house.

154
00:11:35,104 --> 00:11:37,438
Somewhere inside
I knew this about you.

155
00:11:37,632 --> 00:11:39,771
First of all, can you please
calm down?

156
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:41,560
Because I did not
sleep with her.

157
00:11:41,759 --> 00:11:43,766
Secondly, we've had problems
for over a year.

158
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:46,333
And I know you don't wanna deal
with that, but we have.

159
00:11:46,528 --> 00:11:49,374
Oh, I am well aware we've
had problems for the last year.

160
00:11:49,566 --> 00:11:52,284
If I work a little bit too much,
I never stop hearing about it.

161
00:11:52,479 --> 00:11:54,781
But if you work too much,
maestro...

162
00:11:54,974 --> 00:11:57,756
...it's for the sake of your music.
- "Lf" you work too much?

163
00:11:57,950 --> 00:11:59,674
Amanda, you cut
75 trailers this year.

164
00:11:59,871 --> 00:12:02,685
You put a cutting room in the house
and sleep with your BlackBerry.

165
00:12:02,878 --> 00:12:04,983
And I'm not gonna have
a conversation about sex...

166
00:12:05,181 --> 00:12:07,068
...because I can't remember
the last time we did it.

167
00:12:07,262 --> 00:12:09,650
Come on, nobody has time for sex.

168
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:12,221
That's not entirely true.

169
00:12:12,637 --> 00:12:14,972
That's it!
You absolutely slept with her!

170
00:12:15,165 --> 00:12:16,823
Seriously, you have to get out.

171
00:12:17,021 --> 00:12:17,948
Oh, God.

172
00:12:18,141 --> 00:12:19,996
You know what I really think, Ethan?

173
00:12:20,188 --> 00:12:22,937
- I don't think you ever really loved me.
- Oh, please.

174
00:12:23,133 --> 00:12:27,442
You loved the idea of you and me, but
not so much me. Not me, not really.

175
00:12:27,644 --> 00:12:31,222
Look, I did the best I could.
Is anybody good enough for that job?

176
00:12:33,212 --> 00:12:35,994
I will send you your things.

177
00:12:37,627 --> 00:12:39,514
You know you do this, right?

178
00:12:39,707 --> 00:12:42,609
I mean, you screw up
every relationship you've ever been in.

179
00:12:42,811 --> 00:12:44,240
It's what you do.

180
00:12:46,362 --> 00:12:49,362
You didn't really wanna be a couple!
You resist it in your own way!

181
00:12:49,562 --> 00:12:50,741
Shut up!

182
00:12:50,939 --> 00:12:52,978
And it's hard to detect
how you even do it...

183
00:12:53,178 --> 00:12:55,699
...because nobody's quite
as smart as you!

184
00:12:56,122 --> 00:12:58,009
So you're hard to catch at it.

185
00:12:58,202 --> 00:13:00,885
But it always surfaces
and this is what happens.

186
00:13:01,082 --> 00:13:03,318
- What happens?
- Things end.

187
00:13:03,514 --> 00:13:05,139
Just like you knew they would.

188
00:13:05,338 --> 00:13:08,436
Amanda, you know how I feel
about you. There's nobody like you.

189
00:13:08,633 --> 00:13:10,455
You just don't wanna be
what I need.

190
00:13:10,650 --> 00:13:11,991
- Well, not what I "need."
- What?

191
00:13:12,184 --> 00:13:14,094
I mean...
You know what I mean.

192
00:13:14,297 --> 00:13:17,460
You know, I would never cheat on you,
not under any conditions.

193
00:13:17,657 --> 00:13:19,151
Neither would I, okay?

194
00:13:19,352 --> 00:13:22,069
Look at me. I'm down here
sweating like a pig. And look at you.

195
00:13:22,265 --> 00:13:24,850
The only woman on Earth
who breaks up with her boyfriend...

196
00:13:25,049 --> 00:13:27,219
...and doesn't even shed a tear?

197
00:13:27,417 --> 00:13:29,326
I mean,
that's gotta mean something, right?

198
00:13:29,528 --> 00:13:32,430
Why does it bug you so much
that I can't cry?

199
00:13:34,744 --> 00:13:36,402
Esophageal spasm.

200
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,606
Oh, God, it's a big one.

201
00:13:40,183 --> 00:13:44,972
- No, it's okay. I'll be all right.
- I know, I know. I'm thinking about me.

202
00:13:45,175 --> 00:13:47,509
Ethan. Look, it's over.

203
00:13:47,702 --> 00:13:50,320
You know, we might as well
be honest with each other.

204
00:13:50,518 --> 00:13:52,460
Just tell me.

205
00:13:53,175 --> 00:13:55,029
Did you sleep with her?

206
00:13:55,958 --> 00:13:57,268
Just say it.

207
00:13:57,462 --> 00:14:00,910
What's the difference at this point,
right? I mean, why torture me?

208
00:14:01,654 --> 00:14:04,207
Just put me out of my misery.

209
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:08,010
- What are we doing here...?
- Okay.

210
00:14:12,148 --> 00:14:16,621
Yes, okay? I slept with her.
Are you happy?

211
00:14:16,821 --> 00:14:20,715
I've been sleeping with her.
She's in love with me. She's young.

212
00:14:20,917 --> 00:14:23,600
Look, this is not a proud moment
for me.

213
00:14:23,796 --> 00:14:25,552
I mean, you should just know that.

214
00:14:27,859 --> 00:14:29,834
Amanda!

215
00:14:37,107 --> 00:14:38,416
Did you say, am I happy?

216
00:14:38,611 --> 00:14:41,840
I didn't mean that. You get me nuts
sometimes, I say things I don't mean.

217
00:14:42,035 --> 00:14:43,693
In the world of love, Ethan...

218
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:45,582
...not that I'm such a genius at it...

219
00:14:45,779 --> 00:14:48,626
...but in the world of love,
cheating is not acceptable.

220
00:14:48,818 --> 00:14:50,128
No matter what you think...

221
00:14:50,322 --> 00:14:54,000
I know you have a very high opinion
of yourself, but this isn't all me.

222
00:14:54,194 --> 00:14:56,649
- Okay.
- So when you're not in such a rage...

223
00:14:56,850 --> 00:14:59,119
...I think you'll see that too.
- Yeah, maybe.

224
00:14:59,314 --> 00:15:02,794
Maybe when I stop having visions
of you two together...

225
00:15:02,993 --> 00:15:04,619
...I will see your side.

226
00:15:08,945 --> 00:15:10,319
You gotta be...

227
00:15:18,831 --> 00:15:20,588
Punched him in the face.

228
00:15:24,081 --> 00:15:26,185
- Is this a bad time?
- No, no, I'm just...

229
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:28,489
- I'm just flipping out a little bit.
- Oh, okay.

230
00:15:28,687 --> 00:15:31,687
God. Okay... No. I'm okay.
God, why would this happen?

231
00:15:31,887 --> 00:15:33,894
No. You know what? I'm all right.

232
00:15:34,863 --> 00:15:36,292
Hi.

233
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:38,445
What's up?

234
00:15:38,894 --> 00:15:39,942
Ben needs you.

235
00:15:40,271 --> 00:15:42,726
Rebecca Green was just your
average 20-year-old.

236
00:15:42,927 --> 00:15:46,888
Until the father she never knew left
her something she never expected.

237
00:15:47,086 --> 00:15:48,744
Don't scream.

238
00:15:48,942 --> 00:15:51,276
- Your father left you something.
- I never met my father.

239
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:53,990
- Now you know he was interesting.
- Lindsay Lohan.

240
00:15:54,190 --> 00:15:56,197
James Franco.

241
00:15:58,382 --> 00:16:00,138
- Deception.
- You happen to have two guns?

242
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:02,122
