01:13:54,605 --> 01:13:57,452
And then I thought,
maybe this isn't so complicated at all.

984
01:13:57,645 --> 01:13:59,304
And also, I wanted to apologize.

985
01:13:59,501 --> 01:14:01,922
I am sorry I didn't
invite you in this afternoon.

986
01:14:02,124 --> 01:14:04,131
I don't know what that
was about exactly...

987
01:14:04,332 --> 01:14:08,839
...but whatever it was,
I thought that I should just...

988
01:14:10,573 --> 01:14:13,672
Oh, my God. You're,
you're not alone, are you?

989
01:14:15,277 --> 01:14:16,422
No, I'm not, actually.

990
01:14:17,868 --> 01:14:19,428
- I'm sorry.
- No. No, no, no. Don't be.

991
01:14:19,628 --> 01:14:22,149
I shouldn't have just...
Oh, man.

992
01:14:22,349 --> 01:14:25,219
Okay, seriously,
do not worry about this.

993
01:14:25,421 --> 01:14:28,388
This is just me, like, being stupid.

994
01:14:30,092 --> 01:14:31,751
Who is it, Daddy?

995
01:14:33,613 --> 01:14:35,752
- "Daddy"?
- Yes.

996
01:14:35,949 --> 01:14:38,087
I am Daddy.

997
01:14:39,821 --> 01:14:42,187
Amanda, this is my
daughter Sophie.

998
01:14:42,380 --> 01:14:43,787
Soph, this is my friend Amanda.

999
01:14:43,981 --> 01:14:46,436
- Hi.
- How do you do?

1000
01:14:50,061 --> 01:14:52,515
I'm fine, thank you. How are you?

1001
01:14:53,036 --> 01:14:55,175
Very well, thank you.
Do you want to come in?

1002
01:14:55,373 --> 01:14:56,747
Oh, no, I just...

1003
01:14:57,484 --> 01:14:58,467
Hi.

1004
01:14:59,244 --> 01:15:00,389
Come here.

1005
01:15:01,515 --> 01:15:03,621
Daddy, who is this?

1006
01:15:03,820 --> 01:15:08,742
This is Amanda. And, Amanda,
this is my youngest. Olivia.

1007
01:15:13,996 --> 01:15:16,232
Sophie and Olivia.

1008
01:15:16,428 --> 01:15:17,835
Dad.

1009
01:15:18,028 --> 01:15:20,964
- Dad.
- Sorry, yes. Of course, come in.

1010
01:15:21,165 --> 01:15:22,540
Come in.

1011
01:15:25,197 --> 01:15:26,625
Okay.

1012
01:15:32,876 --> 01:15:35,691
Daddy, can we still have
hot chocolate, please?

1013
01:15:35,885 --> 01:15:37,641
- Yes.
- With baby marshmallows?

1014
01:15:37,837 --> 01:15:39,364
Yes.

1015
01:15:49,261 --> 01:15:51,149
Dad, take her coat.

1016
01:15:51,821 --> 01:15:55,497
- Yes. May I, may I...
- Oh, sure. Thanks.

1017
01:15:55,692 --> 01:15:58,474
Are you married? Tell me fast.

1018
01:15:58,668 --> 01:16:00,195
- No.
- Okay.

1019
01:16:03,819 --> 01:16:05,861
I know. I'm a tad overdressed.

1020
01:16:06,061 --> 01:16:07,948
You look like my Barbie.

1021
01:16:10,925 --> 01:16:12,997
- Thanks.
- Is that for us?

1022
01:16:14,348 --> 01:16:17,730
Yes. Except for I'm sorry
about the wine.

1023
01:16:25,643 --> 01:16:28,196
I apologize for not
having mentioned this earlier.

1024
01:16:28,396 --> 01:16:31,265
You're D-l-V-O-R-C-E-D?

1025
01:16:33,227 --> 01:16:36,741
W-l-D-O-W-E-R.

1026
01:16:37,292 --> 01:16:38,950
Two years ago.

1027
01:16:42,923 --> 01:16:47,113
Amanda, are you by any chance
at all into hot chocolate?

1028
01:16:49,260 --> 01:16:52,010
As a matter of fact, I'm...

1029
01:16:52,492 --> 01:16:54,216
...totally into it.

1030
01:16:54,604 --> 01:16:57,059
- Here we go, Olivia. Olivia...
- Thank you.

1031
01:16:57,260 --> 01:16:58,471
...blow on it. It's hot.

1032
01:17:00,588 --> 01:17:02,213
You too, Soph.

1033
01:17:02,540 --> 01:17:04,000
She has more marshmallows
than me.

1034
01:17:04,204 --> 01:17:06,026
No, she doesn't.
You each have five.

1035
01:17:06,604 --> 01:17:08,547
- You have five too.
- Thank you.

1036
01:17:08,748 --> 01:17:11,748
One, two, three, four, five.

1037
01:17:16,812 --> 01:17:18,851
What? Do I have something
on my lip?

1038
01:17:19,627 --> 01:17:21,189
Just look! There.

1039
01:17:23,340 --> 01:17:25,195
- Oh, hello.
- Hello.

1040
01:17:25,388 --> 01:17:28,289
- Hello.
- Going up! Blow on mine.

1041
01:17:30,252 --> 01:17:32,074
Thank you.

1042
01:17:32,267 --> 01:17:33,413
Excellent timing.

1043
01:17:34,154 --> 01:17:37,003
Dad, do Mr. Napkin Head.

1044
01:17:37,196 --> 01:17:39,584
- No. No, no, no. No Mr. Napkin Head.
- Please? Do it!

1045
01:17:39,788 --> 01:17:43,083
- Do it. Do it. Please.
- Do it, please. Beg you, please?

1046
01:17:43,275 --> 01:17:45,927
Please? Okay, I'll do it quickly.

1047
01:17:46,124 --> 01:17:48,644
- Oh, well, thank you for that.
- You're welcome. Now do it.

1048
01:17:48,843 --> 01:17:50,306
All right.

1049
01:17:51,499 --> 01:17:54,085
Amanda, can I borrow
your napkin, please?

1050
01:17:54,284 --> 01:17:55,461
Yes.

1051
01:17:55,884 --> 01:17:57,257
Your glasses.

1052
01:17:57,451 --> 01:17:58,858
Pass me those when I need them.

1053
01:17:59,051 --> 01:18:01,157
Amanda, you're gonna love this.

1054
01:18:01,355 --> 01:18:05,512
It's so funny. I mean, you'll fall
off your chair, it's so funny.

1055
01:18:06,572 --> 01:18:08,066
Hello.

1056
01:18:10,188 --> 01:18:12,904
Hello, my name is Mr. Napkin Head.

1057
01:18:13,708 --> 01:18:16,228
- Hello, children.
- Who's this? She's a stranger?

1058
01:18:16,427 --> 01:18:18,696
- Amanda.
- And why has she got a funny accent?

1059
01:18:18,891 --> 01:18:21,281
- Amanda.
- Yeah, but where is she from?

1060
01:18:22,700 --> 01:18:25,667
Now smoke!

1061
01:18:26,444 --> 01:18:28,102
Go on.

1062
01:18:32,075 --> 01:18:33,897
Smoking's really bad for you.

1063
01:18:36,172 --> 01:18:38,113
Amanda, guess what.

1064
01:18:38,315 --> 01:18:41,066
We have a tent in our playroom.
Do you want to see it?

1065
01:18:41,259 --> 01:18:43,168
No, no, no. Amanda...

1066
01:18:43,372 --> 01:18:46,437
...will not crawl into your tent.

1067
01:18:46,955 --> 01:18:49,825
You don't like tents?

1068
01:18:58,827 --> 01:19:00,999
Okay, this is seriously cool.

1069
01:19:01,195 --> 01:19:03,082
Come inside.

1070
01:19:06,667 --> 01:19:07,943
- Lie down.
- Okay.

1071
01:19:08,139 --> 01:19:10,921
Here, Amanda.
You can use my pillow.

1072
01:19:11,115 --> 01:19:12,544
- Thank you.
- Lie down!

1073
01:19:12,747 --> 01:19:14,470
Can you please
stop being so bossy?

1074
01:19:14,667 --> 01:19:18,015
- Lie down, please, next to me.
- Okay.

1075
01:19:22,828 --> 01:19:25,031
Very nice.

1076
01:19:25,675 --> 01:19:27,780
Excuse me.

1077
01:19:30,411 --> 01:19:33,727
This is an exceptionally great tent.

1078
01:19:33,931 --> 01:19:35,208
It's got something, hasn't it?

1079
01:19:35,404 --> 01:19:38,305
- It's cozy.
- Yeah.

1080
01:19:38,507 --> 01:19:40,579
Who cut out
all these beautiful stars?

1081
01:19:41,163 --> 01:19:43,749
- We did.
- The Three Musketeers!

1082
01:19:54,699 --> 01:19:56,074
Amanda?

1083
01:19:56,650 --> 01:19:58,919
- Yes?
- You smell lovely.

1084
01:19:59,114 --> 01:20:00,260
Do I?

1085
01:20:00,459 --> 01:20:04,966
Yes. I love perfume,
but he won't let me wear it.

1086
01:20:05,164 --> 01:20:07,880
Because you already smell so good.

1087
01:20:08,075 --> 01:20:10,595
- So do you, by the way.
- Thanks.

1088
01:20:10,794 --> 01:20:14,340
- But I'm older, so I guess I'm allowed.
- Exactly.

1089
01:20:14,923 --> 01:20:16,963
I like your eye shadow.

1090
01:20:17,162 --> 01:20:18,472
Thank you.

1091
01:20:18,986 --> 01:20:21,321
- And your lipstick.
- Thank you.

1092
01:20:21,515 --> 01:20:24,362
- It's new.
- What's it called?

1093
01:20:24,555 --> 01:20:28,002
I think it's called Berry Kiss.

1094
01:20:28,203 --> 01:20:30,690
Very Berry Kiss it is.

1095
01:20:32,043 --> 01:20:34,017
Berry Kiss.

1096
01:20:35,531 --> 01:20:37,898
Let's see? It looks good on you.

1097
01:20:38,091 --> 01:20:39,301
Amanda?

1098
01:20:40,587 --> 01:20:43,816
You know, if you wanted to sleep over,
that would be all right.

1099
01:20:44,010 --> 01:20:45,472
We could push our beds together.

1100
01:20:46,891 --> 01:20:48,451
Sorry.

1101
01:20:49,419 --> 01:20:51,274
That's so sweet of you
to invite me...

1102
01:20:51,466 --> 01:20:54,762
...but maybe another time.
Would that be all right?

1103
01:20:55,275 --> 01:20:56,802
Yes.

1104
01:20:59,307 --> 01:21:01,095
Good girl.

1105
01:21:04,394 --> 01:21:07,427
We never have grownups here
that are girls.

1106
01:21:07,947 --> 01:21:08,994
I know.

1107
01:21:09,546 --> 01:21:11,335
I really like it.

1108
01:21:11,530 --> 01:21:14,018
Me too.

1109
01:21:32,266 --> 01:21:35,398
I can't imagine anyone being
a bigger hit with my children.

1110
01:21:37,227 --> 01:21:38,438
They're really great, Graham.

1111
01:21:39,243 --> 01:21:42,025
Sophie's unfortunately taken
on the role as my protector.

1112
01:21:42,218 --> 01:21:45,350
She's brilliant, but I hate it
when she worries about me.

1113
01:21:45,546 --> 01:21:47,073
And Olivia's...

1114
01:21:47,274 --> 01:21:49,379
...gonna be a real ball-buster.

1115
01:21:49,579 --> 01:21:52,447
Which, I must admit,
I kind of love about her.

1116
01:21:53,387 --> 01:21:55,907
I'm trying to figure out
why you didn't tell me about them.

1117
01:21:57,899 --> 01:22:00,354
Because I just don't usually
tell women about them.

1118
01:22:00,554 --> 01:22:02,441
But it's just a little confusing...

1119
01:22:02,634 --> 01:22:05,156
...because you're the one
who wanted to go out to lunch...

1120
01:22:05,355 --> 01:22:06,784
...to get to know one another.

1121
01:22:06,987 --> 01:22:09,834
When you put it that way,
it sounds awful.

1122
01:22:10,250 --> 01:22:14,505
I have no defense. Except that until
I get to know someone really well...

1123
01:22:14,698 --> 01:22:16,967
...it's easier for me to
be a normal, single guy.

1124
01:22:17,162 --> 01:22:20,937
Because it's way too complicated
to be who I really am.

1125
01:22:21,450 --> 01:22:23,272
I'm a full-time dad.

1126
01:22:23,466 --> 01:22:26,564
I'm a working parent.
I'm a mother and a father.

1127
01:22:26,762 --> 01:22:30,690
I'm a guy who reads parenting books
and cookbooks before I go to sleep.

1128
01:22:30,891 --> 01:22:34,239
I spend my weekends buying tutus.
I'm learning to sew.

1129
01:22:34,442 --> 01:22:36,003
I'm Mr. Napkin Head!

1130
01:22:36,202 --> 01:22:39,911
I'm on some kind of
constant overload and it helps...

1131
01:22:40,809 --> 01:22:44,606
...to compartmentalize my life.
Just till I figure this out.

1132
01:22:45,226 --> 01:22:47,844
This past weekend, the children
were with their grandparents.

1133
01:22:48,394 --> 01:22:50,980
And when they're gone,
I get to be somebody...

1134
01:22:51,178 --> 01:22:54,211
...who doesn't have hot chocolate
spilled on his jeans.

1135
01:22:55,049 --> 01:22:58,661
I have no idea how to date
and be this.

1136
01:22:59,082 --> 01:23:01,024
And I suppose there's...

1137
01:23:02,250 --> 01:23:04,552
...the possibility I'm afraid
of what another person...

1138
01:23:04,746 --> 01:23:06,851
...might do to who we are...

1139
01:23:07,050 --> 01:23:09,385
...and how we get from
one day to the next.

1140
01:23:13,897 --> 01:23:15,174
Yeah.

1141
01:23:16,265 --> 01:23:19,364
I guess since I am
leaving in a week, I...

1142
01:23:20,235 --> 01:23:22,503
I sort of get you not telling me.

1143
01:23:23,370 --> 01:23:26,370
- Sort of.
- I thought it would be hard...

1144
01:23:26,570 --> 01:23:29,320
...to introduce them to someone
I may never see again.

1145
01:23:34,666 --> 01:23:36,040
Right.

1146
01:23:36,522 --> 01:23:40,712
Because I'm just someone you had
sex with once and slept with twice.

1147
01:23:40,906 --> 01:23:45,248
I thought I was just someone you had
sex with once and slept with twice.

1148
01:23:45,450 --> 01:23:47,075
Oh, man.

1149
01:23:48,746 --> 01:23:51,168
I think we just went
way past complicated.

1150
01:23:51,370 --> 01:23:55,526
Right. I'm a book editor
from London. You're a...

1151
01:23:56,297 --> 01:23:57,824
...beautiful...

1152
01:23:58,025 --> 01:24:00,993
...movie trailer-maker from L.A.

1153
01:24:01,834 --> 01:24:03,972
We're worlds apart.

1154
01:24:04,746 --> 01:24:06,720
I have a cow in the back yard.

1155
01:24:07,370 --> 01:24:09,060
- You have a cow?
- Yeah.

1156
01:24:09,258 --> 01:24:11,811
I sew and I have a cow.

1157
01:24:12,009 --> 01:24:14,376
How's that for hard to relate to?

1158
01:24:18,249 --> 01:24:20,073
Pretty up there.

1159
01:24:21,545 --> 01:24:23,105
Exactly.

1160
01:24:36,234 --> 01:24:37,728
- Morning, Jesus.
- Good morning.

1161
01:24:37,929 --> 01:24:39,751
- Santa Anas?
- Oh, yeah, long time now.

1162
01:24:39,945 --> 01:24:42,214
- Hi, Marta.
- Hi, Iris.

1163
01:24:45,290 --> 01:24:46,663
Hi there.

1164
01:24:47,593 --> 01:24:49,185
Hello!

1165
01:24:50,154 --> 01:24:51,495
Good morning.

1166
01:24:51,689 --> 01:24:53,347
I counted.

1167
01:24:53,546 --> 01:24:55,684
Nine movies are opening today.

1168
01:24:55,881 --> 01:24:58,598
I remember when nine movies
would open in a month.

1169
01:24:58,793 --> 01:25:04,127
Now a picture has to make a killing
the first weekend or they're dead.

1170
01:25:04,329 --> 01:25:07,013
This is supposed to be conducive
to great work?

1171
01:25:07,210 --> 01:25:10,374
Arthur, have you always
been this feisty?

1172
01:25:10,569 --> 01:25:13,569
Well, I may have slowed down
a little, but yes.

1173
01:25:13,769 --> 01:25:15,973
You've gotta fight the fight, kid.

1174
01:25:16,937 --> 01:25:17,984
Okay, your mail.

1175
01:25:18,538 --> 01:25:21,571
Gas company, phone bill.

1176
01:25:21,770 --> 01:25:25,185
And a letter from the
Writers Guild of America, West.

1177
01:25:28,105 --> 01:25:29,959
Are you watching the movies
I recommended?

1178
01:25:30,154 --> 01:25:33,950
Yes! Love them.
Irene Dunne is fantastic.

1179
01:25:34,152 --> 01:25:37,284
- Gumption.
- Oh, my God, tons of it.

1180
01:25:37,865 --> 01:25:40,767
Arthur, don't you want to open that
letter you just threw in the bin?

1181
01:25:40,970 --> 01:25:43,358
No. They keep writing me
about the same thing.

1182
01:25:43,561 --> 01:25:45,022
But it might be important.

1183
01:25:45,225 --> 01:25:49,862
It's not. They want to arrange
some kind of tribute to me.

1184
01:25:50,057 --> 01:25:51,749
A night with me.

1185
01:25:51,945 --> 01:25:53,506
I don't know. It sounds God-awful.

1186
01:25:53,705 --> 01:25:56,454
What are you talking about?
That sounds brilliant!

1187
01:25:56,648 --> 01:26:02,213
Would you like to walk out on a stage,
on a walker, looking 100 years old...

1188
01:26:02,408 --> 01:26:05,224
...and see 11 schnooks
who showed up just to see you?

1189
01:26:05,418 --> 01:26:07,108
They can forget it.

1190
01:26:07,305 --> 01:26:09,093
I ain't falling for this.

1191
01:26:09,289 --> 01:26:12,585
So now, what's up?

1192
01:26:12,969 --> 01:26:14,430
May I?

1193
01:26:19,529 --> 01:26:21,416
"An Evening With Arthur Abbott."

1194
01:26:23,081 --> 01:26:26,496
"Dear Mr. Abbott...... several
attempts to contact you regarding..."

1195
01:26:26,697 --> 01:26:29,512
"We have not yet received
your response.

1196
01:26:30,537 --> 01:26:32,904
This special night
will be a tribute to your...

1197
01:26:33,096 --> 01:26:36,992
...lifetime screenwriting achievement
and contribution to the profession.

1198
01:26:37,193 --> 01:26:40,040
Congratulations on this
much-deserved honor."

1199
01:26:40,681 --> 01:26:42,404
Arthur, this is a big deal.

1200
01:26:42,601 --> 01:26:44,673
You know, and they want
to do this soon.

1201
01:26:45,512 --> 01:26:48,644
Listen, I reckon
that with a little bit of exercise...

1202
01:26:48,840 --> 01:26:50,434
...you could walk out on your own.

1203
01:26:50,633 --> 01:26:53,088
And, you know,
maybe I could go with you.

1204
01:26:53,288 --> 01:26:56,256
As, like, your date or something.

1205
01:26:56,457 --> 01:26:59,904
I would take you proudly,
my darling, but I'm not going.

1206
01:27:00,744 --> 01:27:05,252
Anyway, how would you propose
to get me in shape? Seriously.

1207
01:27:06,409 --> 01:27:07,620
Easy.

1208
01:27:08,681 --> 01:27:10,753
You're doing really well.

1209
01:27:10,953 --> 01:27:14,499
Nearly there. Nearly there.
Nearly there.

1210
01:27:14,697 --> 01:27:17,958
Bravo! Here we go,
back the other way.

1211
01:27:23,721 --> 01:27:25,663
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

1212
01:27:25,864 --> 01:27:28,231
- You sure?
- Yeah, I just slipped.

1213
01:27:48,168 --> 01:27:50,308
- Hello?
- So are you ever coming home?

1214
01:27:50,505 --> 01:27:52,610
- Oh, my God. Hi.
- How's it going?

1215
01:27:52,809 --> 01:27:54,182
Great. I met a really nice guy.

1216
01:27:54,377 --> 01:27:56,547
See? And you said you'd never.
What's he like?

1217
01:27:56,744 --> 01:27:58,882
He's really cute. I feel great
when I'm with him...

1218
01:27:59,080 --> 01:28:02,942
...which is an entirely new experience.
And he's about 90 years old.

1219
01:28:03,144 --> 01:28:04,967
- Come on.
- He' my next-door neighbor.

1220
01:28:05,161 --> 01:28:08,227
Or Amanda's next-door neighbor.
By the way, you should go meet her.

1221
01:28:08,872 --> 01:28:12,417
- Yeah. I have, actually.
- Oh, bugger. Call waiting.

1222
01:28:12,616 --> 01:28:15,431
Can you hold for a sec? Hold on.
I really wanna talk to you.

1223
01:28:15,624 --> 01:28:17,347
- Sure.
- Hello.

1224
01:28:17,544 --> 01:28:20,611
- Iris, hi, it's Amanda.
- How are you? How's it going?

1225
